name: Room in Mejiro/Ikebukuro (2of2) for 1 person
description:
· 7-min walk from Mejiro Station on JR Yamanote line
· 15-min walk to Ikebukuro, a hub city in Tokyo
· Quiet and comfortable residential area with supermarkets, restaurants etc.
· This room suits 1 person
· Non-smokers only please
neighborhood_overview:
· An ideal neighborhood coveted even by locals! A quiet residential area nestled in the heart of Tokyo with quick and easy access to the JR Yamanote Line and major metropolitan centers and attractions. Perfect for travelers who want to immerse themselves in the chaos of the city by day and come home to a quiet home at night for rest.
· Plenty of cute side streets, parks, shops etc. to explore in the immediate area, if you don't feel like venturing too far. Guests often tell me about a restaurant or pub they've discovered close to the house that I didn't even know was there!
· Shinjuku, the biggest city in the Tokyo area, is 3 stops away on the Yamanote Line; Ikebukuro, another large, bustling city, is a short walk (10-15 mins) from the house.
· From Mejiro Station to my house is about a 7-minute walk. When you book your room, I will provide detailed instructions for getting to the house, both from Mejiro Station and from Haneda and Narita Airports. The instructions are c
host_about:
Hello, travelers!

I am a fun, easy-going Tokyo native who enjoys meeting people from all over the world and hearing about their lives, cultures, and experiences. My interests include languages, culture, literature, economics, exercise, cooking, and traveling. I have lived in Mejiro most of my life, so you’ll be staying with a true local.
I’m often outside the house for work or visiting friends and family, but whenever I’m home I look forward to hanging out and enjoying good conversation with my guests. I’ve met so many interesting people since I start hosting!

I have two daughters named Yuna (born in 2016) and Yuki (2019).

Any guests who don’t mind kids around are welcome!

I have three rooms available through Airbnb, so please check for all my listings if the first one you see doesn’t suit your schedule.
We hope you have a wonderful time in Japan!

name: #2 Workdesk/Discover local life, culture & People
description:
Finally, the bordar was opened!

Hi, this is Toshi, an English speaker. Welcome to this neighborhood and my home. This area, called YaNeSen(Yanaka, Sendagi, Nezu), has preserved the charm as creating a contrast of old and new at the same time. It's because of the tendency to re-purpose older buildings rather than rebuilding. My home is a big house in good condition even located in central Tokyo. I manage this house as enjoying sharing life. In a word, the best place to feel local life in Tokyo.
neighborhood_overview:
Super convenient location to get around Tokyo.
6 min walk from the nearest subway station.
A gate area to central Tokyo from airport.

Here is a remaining authentic downtown in Tokyo. A quiet neighborhood with one of the most vivid local market street in Tokyo, beautiful sakura-lined cemetery, plenty of temples, old and new indie cafes, restaurants, shops and stalls, some of which have passed down through generations, and art galleries, etc. All of them are within 1-15 mins walking distance. So now here attracts both Japanese and foreigner visitors so much. Just lovely area.

- Local shopping street, Yanaka Ginza (10 mins walk)
- Yanaka Cemetery (10 mins walk)
- Ueno Park (15 mins walk)
- University of Tokyo (15 mins walk)
- 24/7 convenience store (5 min walk)
- Supermarket (6 min walk)
- Drugstores (3 min walk)
host_about:
Hi there.
A serial entrepreneur since late twenties. After got tired of my work life, shifted to live my life, not for work.
- Managing a share/guest house
- Business and team building trainer in internship and self-developing program
- Providing communication training and self-awareness session

Now preparing a vacation rental / my second house in a country seaside area.  
Down shifted with less money, less stress, more time, more happiness.

neighborhood_overview: Ginza is the most prestagious shopping and cuisine neighborhood in Tokyo, even in Japan. You can enjoy this neighborhood with 5 mins walk. Also our place is located in Yurakucho area in which so many daily use bars, Iazakaya, are located.  You can enjoy both different circumstance in walk-able distance.
host_about:
Now we are running 2 guest rooms in major spots in Tokyo, Kagurazaka and Ginza. Both the neighborhoods have interesting historical background and best accumulations of the best cuisines, shops, and cultural facilities. 
We are trying to provide you nicely-designed cozy space in the middle of interesting neighborhood. Please enjoy the atmosphere of the town as one of the member of dwellers!

===
[Studio-D, Kagurazaka]

Even thought, Kagurazaka is located in the middle of Tokyo, this neightborehood still has Japanese traditional atmosphere. Visit Kagurazaka to find another face of Tokyo.

The main road of Kagurazaka was once at the outer edge of Edo Castle, opposite the Ushigome bridge over the castle moat, and has always been busy because of this privileged location. In the early 20th century, the area was renowned for its numerous geisha houses, of which several remain today. Currently, Kagurazaka is experiencing a popularity boom due to its traditional, sophisticated atmosphere on the edge of modern Shinjuku ward.

Kagurazaka is also widely regarded as an important center of Japanese cuisine. (2 of triple michelen stars, 3 of double Michelen stars are located in such a small neighborhood!!)
Several old and famous “ryotei” are to be found in the winding back streets, often accessible only by foot. These ryotei provide expensive “kaiseki” cuisine, which is generally regarded as the pinnacle of Japanese food. Ryotei also allow diners to invite geisha to provide entertainment during the course of the evening.
While it retains a traditional Japanese atmosphere, Kagurazaka now boasts a significant French presence with many French expatriates living in the area due to the proximity of l’Institut Franco-Japonais de Tokyo.

===
[WOW-GINZA]

The other one, GINZA, is one of the world famous commercial zone, just like 5th avenue in NYC, Piccadilly Circus in London. You can go into the area with just 5 mins walk from the room.
Not only shopping but there are so many resuaurant in GINZA. As "Opening a restaurant in Ginza" is most of all the restaurant owner's dream, there are many nice and sophisticated restaurants located in this area and competing their skills and plates every night! (2 of triple michelen stars, 15 of double Michelen stars are in GINZA area!) Not only the high-end's plates, but there are also millions of daily use drinking spots (Izakaya) for the office workers. You can enjoy the noise of town covered with chiken BBQ smoke,  on the street side table with a shot of Hot Sake!! 

The room, WOW-GINZA, is by the rail trucks from Tokyo station. You can see all kinds of trains crossing in each 5 mins. You can enjoy another facade of Tokyo!

description:
The Miyake Guest House features a typical Japanese home that was originally designed for two families. Guests will stay at a private, stand alone area with its own kitchen, bathroom and bedrooms. This space is available for full or shared rentals.

Great for groups/families staying in Tokyo long term in a quiet upscale neighborhood, or for somene wishing to experience local living. It's a 7-minute walk to the train station and 10-20 minutes to Kichijoji, Shibuya and Shinjuku.

Hamadayama is a quiet residential area located in the Suginami Ward. Our home is conveniently located 7 min. away from the train station. Everything you need, restaurants, supermarkets, shops, hospitals and parks are all within walking distance.

Our annex towns of Takaido and Nishieifuku also have very good ramen shops and izakayas. There's even hot spring bath in Takaido!
host_about:

We speak Japanese (native), Spanish (fluent) and English (beginner).

I'm Kentaro Kanemaru who work at Rainbow Peaks CO., LTD. (graphic and web managing company). I'm 39 years old, living in Setagaya with my wife Kyoko(She is Hawaiian Hula dancer) and our pretty cat Gabriel. Most of my friends call me “Bambi” I’m so happy if you call me “Bambi”.
I love traveling all over the world. I already have traveled over 40 countries. That's why I start to invite people to my place through Airbnb, I’d like to have many guests from many countries, and communicate with many people from many countries as like you. It is a good opportunity for me to know much more things about Japan what I have not recognized ever. It is also so easy to feel the mood of traveling. I’m so happy if we can share some precious experience. 
Otherwise, My favorite taste is  music, traveling, fashion, cat, art, fixed bike, all kinds of bicycle, skate, climbing, camping, fishing, clubbing, and party.
If you want to enjoy another side of Japan, Please contact me.
I'm sure to show you some interesting Japan.
So I'm really looking forward to having you.

Thank you 
Bambi

name: 皎月山荘・東京　Kougetsu Sanso ---  Moon Villa in Tokyo
description:
"If you look at Tenohara, you may be in the mountains of Mikasa, where Kasuga comes to life." ~ Abe Arashiro

A traditional wooden house tucked away in a quiet residential area.It is a luxurious mountain house where you can enjoy the beautiful original Japanese landscape, such as the chirping of small birds and the flowers that color the four seasons.Located on the south side of Mountain House 1F, the terrace is a luxurious space reminiscent of the "Tsukiwadai" of the Heian nobility.
neighborhood_overview:
Tsukisanso is conveniently located with a single sidewalk from the Takao Kaido.
There are various shops just a short walk away, just like the silence in the mountain villa is a lie.
250m 100yen Lawson
250m refining fire pavilion (barbecue restaurant)
300m Yumean (Japanese Restaurant)
300m Japanese Restaurant (7:00 am ~)
300m Châteletsé (bread and confectionery)
400m Starbucks (7:00 am ~)
400m Chinese Restaurant
400m 7-Eleven

Mt. Takao, Minami Osawa Outlet, Summerland (amusement park) are close by.

Sushi, Soba…
Hot Spring
️ Golf Course
Please let us know if you have any requests.
We will respond to your request as much as possible with our staff.

The roads to Mt. Fuji, Fuji Goko, Gotemba Outlet, Kamakura, Karuizawa, Kusatsu, and Matsumoto Castle arrive smoothly without congestion.

name: 1 bed use in a dormitory with 24 use  Fitness Gym
description:
【In March 2021, a full-scale fitness gym was newly established in the building and reopened!】
Hi! We’re obi Hostel.
This is the best place for the people who want to explore down town of Tokyo, meet other travelers, feel local atmosphere…!
All our staff would like to make your journey! Not only in our hostel, but whole trip in Japan!
If you need any other things, there are convenience store and super market just around the corner!
neighborhood_overview:
obi Hostel is located in the down town area of Tokyo. So you can explore historical spot and feel local atmosphere.
Visit “Asakusa area” which is one of the most famous sightseeing spots in Tokyo. Just 5min from obi by subway, but go there on foot along the “Sumida River”. It may take longer(apx.30min), but flat. What I like is the view from the river side. You can see old, new, low, high buildings and Tokyo Sky Tree. You’ve might been to other countries, but have you ever seen disordered but well-proportioned city, like this Tokyo. Worth to do!
Of course, if you take a subway for 10min, you will be in skyscrapers jungle.

name: 80m2 Nordic Japanese House in Shinjuku
description: Modern, fully equipped, Nordic Japanese style home in a quiet residential area. One train stop to Shinjuku shopping and nightlife districts (Shinjuku Sanchome). Our guests can enjoy a bright, new and spacious house all for themselves. Great for families with kids or groups of friends. Make yourself at home! We will pay for the taxi ride (one taxi only) from Shinjuku to our house at their arrival!
neighborhood_overview: The house is located in a very quiet residential area and surrounded by commercial areas with lots of restaurants, supermarkets, convenience stores and local shops such as bakery, onigiri shops. Easy access to Shinjuku (two stops by train) and other touristic places in the center area of Tokyo. Great for kids to access to Toy Museum, Fire Fighter Museum and parks and play grounds in the area.
host_about: We are a Finnish-Japanese family of four. We love our quiet neighborhood with a nice mix of old and new little shops and restaurants. Our shared passion goes to food and cooking as well as traveling and out-door activities. We love to meet new people, to exchange information on what is going on and where, to share our favorite Tokyo spots for others to enjoy, too. It takes about 45 min. by Keio Line from Shinjuku St. to Minamidaira St., and about 15 to 20 min.on foot from the st. Since it is an uphill, if you have large luggage, you can also take a bus or taxi from Takahatafudo St. It is almost the top of the Mt. It is a nice place surrounded by green.
neighborhood_overview:
There is a big grocery store called “Yaoko” near Minamidaira station, a coin laundry , Seven Eleven, a pizza store, a family restaurant and a beef bowl shop all within a 10-14 minutes walk.

I think that you already know the information of the Takao area through guide books. Since Michel-in's star arrived, Mt. Takao seems to be crowded with a tremendous number of people. If you want to enjoy green trekking and avoid the crowd, there is a 16KM route not in the guidebook.
You can enjoy short treks in the forest of the back of the house. You can walk to the entrance of Tama zoo in about 30 minutes, which you may enjoy visiting. t
host_about:
The beginning of the journey.
I was a steel worker. It was Cleveland, body and mind were frozen.
I never been good at studying, I haven't been able to work well at the company, and I wasn't good at human relations. Everything was bad in Cleveland.
 If you ask me like or dislike whole life in Cleveland,  Of course I say I hate it, but I loved it so much that tears came.
On Christmas holidays, I missed the warmth of the sun and headed south.
I drove Dodge for 30 hours to get away from something.
 I grew up in the Pacific and the sea was blue. The Atlantic I saw for the first time was green. Like the color of your eyes. I'm sorry I couldn't understand you  well.
I was struck by a squall with a hole in the back on the beach in Florida   I was crying without knowing. I wonder what it was.
 A car runs over the sea to Key West. I had a sunset in small island and I ate a pizza. Hey, I can eat olives on the pizza now.
 I thought towards the sunset. "I love you" but I can't say I love you. Can I quit the job? I don't want to go back there. I want to go further south.
She said there is only ocean you can’t go further !
 "Are you okay?"

 Of course I’m not okay,
I know  I’m not okay !

Where am I going?
How far will I reach?
Is there anything beyond the end of the south?
I was 25 years old.

If you are lost in your life, even if you do not know  you are running away or pursuing, I will sincerely congratulate you on your journey.
Even if you don't know what it is. One day I want you to tell me if you discover it, This is between you and me.
I still don't know anything. But maybe you and I were promised to meet on the way.

I want to be a gentle guy just a little more than before.
 I think so now.

Since Ogikubo station was established in 1891 it has been popular as a quiet get-way not far from the hustle of the main Tokyo business and shopping areas.

name: Nomad Hostel Classic / Semi-Private #4
description:
【Our hostel character】

- Cozy and clean hostel renovated from Japanese oriental house
- Affordable price for budget traveler
- 10 minutes walk from Asakusa Sta. but still located in a quiet local areas
- Capsule style dormitory bed with more privacy and more space than typical dorm bed (bunk bed style)
- Air condition and heaters
- Wifi availabe
- Covered pillow, blankets and mattress are provided per bed
- Cleaning time between 10am to 3pm (common areas, dorm room)
neighborhood_overview:
1. 6-7 minutes walk from 2 main Tokyo Metro lines; Asakusa and Ginza
2. 20 second walk to 100yen convenience store Lawson, less than 2 minutes from 7/11
3, 1 minute walk to Laundry shop
4. 4 minutes walk to the nearest Japanese style public bath
5. 15 minutes by walk to famous Tokyo Skytree
6. 5 minutes walk to super market
7. 10 minutes walk to Kaminarimon or Sensouji temple which is the land mark of Asakusa
host_about:
Hello! 
We are Gomez and Kase, 100% Japanese guys who have experienced travelling around south east Asia.

We manage newly opened "Nomad Hostel".
We hope to meet you and share part of your time in Tokyo.

We like hopping around bars and "Izakaya". 

We are so happy if you're interested in traveling to Japan!

See you !

name: New Open Mixed Dorm! Close to Ueno Zoo and Ameyoko
description:
Welcome to The bnb+ Ueno Okachimachi.

“Not just staying, but also a good memory itself to stay”
With such concept, we made “bnb+".

As for the whole hostel, it is a design which imaged the 30's, USA. You can feel as if sleeping in a sleeper train.
neighborhood_overview:
Keisei Ueno station is 5-minute walk away.
From Keisei Use station, you can go to Narita airport directry with Skyliner.

Ueno station is 9-minute walk away.
You can easily go to downtown area in Tokyo(Shinjuku, Shibuya, Ikebukuro, Akihabara..etc)

If you use the subway, you can go to Ginza, Tsukiji, Roppongi, Ningyocho, Ebisu, Nakameguro with a single line!
Ueno Okachimachi (subway station) is also a 3-minute walk away.

There is Ueno Park nearby, and there are famous museums such as the Tokyo Metropolitan Art Museum, the Tokyo National Museum, the National Science Museum and the Ueno Roy Museum.

It is also a short walk to Ameyoko market. Ameyoko is a famous outside market, there are many food stands, discount shops.

Since the hostel is also in downtown area, it is easy to enjoy night life.
neighbourhood: 台東区, 東京都, Japan

neighborhood_overview:
Upon getting out of the Airport (regardless Narita or Haneda) head to the train master's desk and ask for the platform number and time of the direct train going to Asakusa.
Get off at the Asakusa station and connect to the free metro wifi (if no on hand portable wifi device). Using your smart phone, tablet or laptop, simply type in our address to get an idea on how to get to our place.

From Japan: Take Asakusa or Ginza metro line and get off at the Asakusa Station, connect to the free metro wifi (if no on hand portable wifi device). Using your smart phone, tablet or laptop, simply type in our address to get an idea on how to get to our place.

通过Airbnb为世界上各个国家的朋友提供真诚的服务,增加在日本的乐趣是我的愿望｡

description:
"If you pretend to be in the sky, you might go to Mt. Mikasa to see Kasuga" ~ Abe Nakamaru

A traditional wooden house that stands secluded through a quiet residential area.It is a luxurious mountain house where you can have exclusive access to the beautiful original landscape of Japan, such as birds singing and flowers coloring the four seasons.The terrace on the south side of Sanso 1F is a luxurious space reminiscent of the Heian nobility's "Moon's Stand".

Jiaozuokushanso is conveniently located in a single sidewalk from the Takao highway.
There are various stores just a short walk away, as the silence at the Sanso seems to be a lie.
250m 100JPY Lawson

400m Chinese restaurants

Mt. Takao, Minami-Ozawa outlet, Summerland (amusement park) are just around the corner.

Sushi shop, soba shop...
hot spring ️
golf course,
let me know if I can help.
The staff will be available and will do their best to accommodate your request.

neighborhood_overview:
obi Hostel is located in the down town area of Tokyo. So you can explore historical spot and feel local atmosphere.
Visit “Asakusa area” which is one of the most famous sightseeing spots in Tokyo. Just 5min from obi by subway, but go there on foot along the “Sumida River”. It may take longer(apx.30min), but flat. What I like is the view from the river side. You can see old, new, low, high buildings and Tokyo Sky Tree. You’ve might been to other countries, but have you ever seen disordered but well-proportioned city, like this Tokyo. Worth to do!
Of course, if you take a subway for 10min, you will be in skyscrapers jungle.

Access from Airports: my Accommodation is very convenient and almost direct from Narita Airport and Haneda Airport as well as  JR Railway Tokyo St., Nippori St., Shinnjuku,Shibuya,and Ikebukuro St.
Host owners and administrators are bilingual (MBA at NYU), having lived and worked in New York, London and Tokyo for 40 years. You will enjoy our “OMOTENASHI” or “Heartful” Japanese services.

name: 2 private rooms, one living room/Shinagawa, Meguro
description:
Located in a relatively quiet residential area of ​​Takanawa, Minato-ku, Tokyo, and is recommended for couples and families who want to relax.

High-speed wifi, washlet toilet seat, no washing machine but there is laudymatt in front of the house. Equipped with a microwave oven, pot, refrigerator, etc., it is sufficient for daily life (There is NO kitchen).

Your floor is located in 3 and 4th floor without elevator. You need to carry your lagguge by yourself. We will help you when we are here.
neighborhood_overview:
Examples of nearby properties include Izumitake Temple, Zaizeji Temple, National Science Museum Nature Education Park, Tokyo Metropolitan Garden Museum, and Minato-ku Local Museum.Roppongi National Museum of New Art, Roppongi Hills and Midtown are just around the corner.
When you want to breathe, there are a wide variety of cafes and restaurants including Platinum Street's Chocolatier Erica, Basque Gasta, and Finanche's famous Maisondani, with natural yeast bread and exquisite pudding ratrie-cocco.
Convenience stores, 100 yen Lawson, Don Quijote, and more are nearby, making it convenient for shopping.The docomo share cycle is also within a 2-minute walk of the port, making it fun to extend your bike.
It will also be a pleasant time to stroll around Azabu Ten next to the station.
Local owners are familiar with restaurant information. If you need to, we can recommend or make a reservation.

name: 小部屋6（予約前サイズ確認）東京郊外/旅人少/静か/漫画5千.JR新宿駅26分のくにたち駅か立川駅
description:
Imagine the size of the room.
213cm long and 179cm wide (7ft☓5.9ft).
From Shinjuku St. to Kunitachi/Tachikawa St. on the Chuo Line 40 min.
then 15 min. by 100 yen bus from Kunitachi station. 1 minute walk from "Nishimachi 1-chome Kita" bus stop.
It is a 19 min. by walk from Kunitachi Station. It's a little far from Tachikawa station.
No parking lot.
7-Eleven, Growth store 10 min on foot.
heating and cooling equipment in bed room, but not in the living room.
5,000 manga books　
Wifi /TV.
bike1
host_about:
The beginning of the journey.
I was a steel worker. It was Cleveland, body and mind were frozen.
I never been good at studying, I haven't been able to work well at the company, and I wasn't good at human relations. Everything was bad in Cleveland.
 If you ask me like or dislike whole life in Cleveland,  Of course I say I hate it, but I loved it so much that tears came.
On Christmas holidays, I missed the warmth of the sun and headed south.
I drove Dodge for 30 hours to get away from something.
 I grew up in the Pacific and the sea was blue. The Atlantic I saw for the first time was green. Like the color of your eyes. I'm sorry I couldn't understand you  well.
I was struck by a squall with a hole in the back on the beach in Florida   I was crying without knowing. I wonder what it was.
 A car runs over the sea to Key West. I had a sunset in small island and I ate a pizza. Hey, I can eat olives on the pizza now.
 I thought towards the sunset. "I love you" but I can't say I love you. Can I quit the job? I don't want to go back there. I want to go further south.
She said there is only ocean you can’t go further !
 "Are you okay?"

 Of course I’m not okay,
I know  I’m not okay !

Where am I going?
How far will I reach?
Is there anything beyond the end of the south?
I was 25 years old.

If you are lost in your life, even if you do not know  you are running away or pursuing, I will sincerely congratulate you on your journey.
Even if you don't know what it is. One day I want you to tell me if you discover it, This is between you and me.
I still don't know anything. But maybe you and I were promised to meet on the way.

I want to be a gentle guy just a little more than before.
 I think so now.

 I grew up in the Pacific and the sea was blue. The Atlantic I saw for the first time was green. Like the color of your eyes. I'm sorry I couldn't understand you  well.
I was struck by a squall with a hole in the back on the beach in Florida   I was crying without knowing. I wonder what it was.
 A car runs over the sea to Key West. I had a sunset in small island and I ate a pizza. Hey, I can eat olives on the pizza now.
 I thought towards the sunset. "I love you" but I can't say I love you. Can I quit the job? I don't want to go back there. I want to go further south.
She said there is only ocean you can’t go further !
 "Are you okay?"

 Of course I’m not okay,
I know  I’m not okay !

Where am I going?
How far will I reach?
Is there anything beyond the end of the south?
I was 25 years old.

If you are lost in your life, even if you do not know  you are running away or pursuing, I will sincerely congratulate you on your journey.
Even if you don't know what it is. One day I want you to tell me if you discover it, This is between you and me.
I still don't know anything. But maybe you and I were promised to meet on the way.

I want to be a gentle guy just a little more than before.
 I think so now.

The town where Bamba Hotel is located in Shinagawa-cho, Tokaido

Shinagawa Inn was thriving in the Edo period (as the main road connecting Tokyo Nihonbashi and Kyoto Sanjo Ohashi).

The horse stables originated from the horse parking lot that existed at Shinagawa Inn at the time = Bamba.


Once again, people and information stay at Shinagawa Inn and have a relaxing time.

The Bamba Hotel was born in 2014 as a dream of renaissance.

The Bamba Hotel is an 80-year-old house, so there are no restaurants, bars, or large baths.

description:
"Villa in Takanawa, Minato-ku"

Located in a quiet residential neighborhood just one street back from a main street lined with high-rise buildings.A white wooden building beside a large parking lot there. It is a hotel where you can enjoy the freedom of living that is unique to a single house hotel.

Previously loved by the community as an omiya, this building has been loved for 50 years.It was reborn as a single-family hotel with the owner's desire to keep the building intact.

Opened in 2016, Araiya is a 1-minute walk from Izumidakeji Station on the Keikyu Line.
It is a 5-minute walk from Takanawa Gateway Station on the JR Yamanote Line.

It is a modern city with office buildings around it, but it is also a city with a long history.

name: 小さな部屋に、暮らすように滞在してみる。
description:
We have prepared a 3 tatami room in a small house in a quiet residential area.
I will meet you very much like my family and friends.
While thinking about reducing disposable items as much as possible and connecting to the future, we live in a flexible and balanced way.We hope you'll share your ideas with your guests.
I propose a 3-tatami private Japanese style room in a small house in a quiet residential area.
I would like to welcome my guests as a friend and a family member.
I have an eco-friendly lifestyle. I try to recycle my garbage and to minimize disposable items as much as possible. I would be happy to discuss and share stories with my guests.
neighborhood_overview:
Koganei, Tokyo, Japan
It is a quiet neighborhood with many parks and green areas at walking distances from the house, such as Kushino Park, Kuriyama Park, Koganei Park, where locals and families often go to rest, walk and play. There also is a very nice path to walk along the Nogawa river leading to the Nogawa Park.
If you like walking or cycling, you can reach the Tama Lake through a beautiful walking/cycling road with many places to rest on the way.
Koganei is a charming town with many cafes, specialty coffee shops, restaurants and shops.

家の周りには、気分転換やリラックスに最適な緑がたくさん。

Walk along the river, Nogawa Park
If you can walk everywhere, the Goal is Lake Tama
A resting place to rest during a walk...♪

host_about:
I like to travel and to look for interesting places where to stay, while walking around the city enjoying the architecture of buildings and the historical landmarks, looking for local shops and restaurants with homemade meals, learning about local stories and dialects. Motivated by such experiences, I decided to start hosting travelers wishing to help them by providing an accommodation and the opportunity to discover non-touristic places and lifestyle of the locals.

私は､旅先では､観光名所を回ることよりも､散歩をしながら建物や人の様子､ﾛｰｶﾙなｽｰﾊﾟｰや飲食店､方言や家庭料理､そういった土地柄を感じられる滞在先を探して､旅をすることが好きです。その経験から､同じように暮らすような旅のｽﾀｲﾙを楽しみたい人をお手伝い出来たらと思い､民泊を始めることに決めました。リクエストの際には、自己紹介や旅の目的をメッセージに添えていただけますと、嬉しいです。よろしくお願いいたします。

name: Deep Shibuya/Private use house
description:
2 Rooms TOMIGAYA : a detached condo for the Active Tokyo crowlers!

After crossing the scramble crossing and walking through Shibuya Center Street, you will reach an area with a completely different atmosphere, the deep Shibuya with stylish excitement and calmfulness.

The pedestrian promenade pathing through leads you to one of the coolest neighborhood in Tokyo, Tomigaya, with the cutting edge stores and fashionable cafes.
You can enjoy Tokyo life actively regardless of the time of day.
host_about:
Now we are running 2 guest rooms in major spots in Tokyo, Kagurazaka and Ginza. Both the neighborhoods have interesting historical background and best accumulations of the best cuisines, shops, and cultural facilities. 
We are trying to provide you nicely-designed cozy space in the middle of interesting neighborhood. Please enjoy the atmosphere of the town as one of the member of dwellers!

===
[Studio-D, Kagurazaka]

Even thought, Kagurazaka is located in the middle of Tokyo, this neightborehood still has Japanese traditional atmosphere. Visit Kagurazaka to find another face of Tokyo.

The main road of Kagurazaka was once at the outer edge of Edo Castle, opposite the Ushigome bridge over the castle moat, and has always been busy because of this privileged location. In the early 20th century, the area was renowned for its numerous geisha houses, of which several remain today. Currently, Kagurazaka is experiencing a popularity boom due to its traditional, sophisticated atmosphere on the edge of modern Shinjuku ward.

Kagurazaka is also widely regarded as an important center of Japanese cuisine. (2 of triple michelen stars, 3 of double Michelen stars are located in such a small neighborhood!!)
Several old and famous “ryotei” are to be found in the winding back streets, often accessible only by foot. These ryotei provide expensive “kaiseki” cuisine, which is generally regarded as the pinnacle of Japanese food. Ryotei also allow diners to invite geisha to provide entertainment during the course of the evening.
While it retains a traditional Japanese atmosphere, Kagurazaka now boasts a significant French presence with many French expatriates living in the area due to the proximity of l’Institut Franco-Japonais de Tokyo.

===
[WOW-GINZA]

The other one, GINZA, is one of the world famous commercial zone, just like 5th avenue in NYC, Piccadilly Circus in London. You can go into the area with just 5 mins walk from the room.
Not only shopping but there are so many resuaurant in GINZA. As "Opening a restaurant in Ginza" is most of all the restaurant owner's dream, there are many nice and sophisticated restaurants located in this area and competing their skills and plates every night! (2 of triple michelen stars, 15 of double Michelen stars are in GINZA area!) Not only the high-end's plates, but there are also millions of daily use drinking spots (Izakaya) for the office workers. You can enjoy the noise of town covered with chiken BBQ smoke,  on the street side table with a shot of Hot Sake!! 

The room, WOW-GINZA, is by the rail trucks from Tokyo station. You can see all kinds of trains crossing in each 5 mins. You can enjoy another facade of Tokyo!

description:

- Wants to experience daily life and culture, not just a tourist trip
- Has just arrived in Japan and wants a roommate until they get accustomed to life in Japan

- Flat sharing with friendly host who speaks English in
- Located in Hiroo, an international and quiet upscale residential area

- Able to speak English
- Interested in making local friends

- Conduct a web interview or tour

host_about:
I moved to Venezuela after university and spent the next 25 years there. I was fortunate to live in a diverse neighborhood where I had the chance to meet people from many different cultures which I truly enjoyed.
We decided to open up our space upstairs to once again welcome the opportunity and meet people from all over the world.
We speak Japanese (native), Spanish (fluent) and English (beginner).
